OpenPhone uses a dual-license model for OpenPhone-owned materials.

1. Non-commercial license

   OpenPhone-owned materials are made available for non-commercial use under
   the PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0. See LICENSE.noncommercial.

   SPDX-License-Identifier: PolyForm-Noncommercial-1.0.0

2. Commercial license

   Commercial use of OpenPhone-owned materials requires a separate written
   commercial license from the OpenPhone project owner. See COMMERCIAL.md.

3. Upstream and third-party materials

   This repository also contains patch files, references, build integration,
   and documentation related to Android, LineageOS, Linux, device trees, vendor
   extraction flows, and other third-party projects. OpenPhone does not
   relicense materials it did not create.

   Upstream and third-party materials keep their original licenses. Apache,
   BSD, MIT, GPL, proprietary vendor blob, and other notices must be preserved
   according to the relevant upstream license.

4. GPL-covered materials

   GPL-covered code and modifications remain subject to the GPL. OpenPhone does
   not add non-commercial restrictions to GPL-covered code.

5. File-specific overrides

   If a file contains a different license notice, that file-specific notice
   controls for that file.
